<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00553</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO STRENGHTEN THE OFFICE OF THE OMBUDSMAN BY ENHANCING FISCAL AUTONOMY, UPGRADING EMPLOYEE SKILLS, AND AUGMENTING COMPENSATION, ALLOWANCES AND BENEFITS, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 6770, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE OMBUDSMAN ACT OF 1989, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Strengthening the Office of the Ombudsman Act. Appropriates initially the sum of P1.8 billion to increase the salaries of the Office of the Ombudsman on the same level as that of the Judiciary and the same amount shall be added to the annual budget of the Office for the following years.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>DEL MAR, RAUL V.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Chipeco (019 2016-09-06)</td><td>2. Dalipe (000 2018-07-31)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS ON 2016-07-27</td></tr></table>